# CODEOWNERS — engine vs product partition per ADR 0037 + Issue #80.
#
# Solo-dev today; this file's load-bearing value lands when a second
# contributor joins. GitHub uses CODEOWNERS to auto-request review on
# PRs that touch matching paths. The partition documented in CLAUDE.md
# (engine = build apparatus; product = curriculum / pedagogy / schema)
# becomes mechanically enforced at that boundary.
#
# When a second contributor joins:
#   - Replace the per-partition single-owner lines with the appropriate
#     reviewers for each tree.
#   - Promote this file's authoring to an ADR (engine-side; the rationale
#     for the partition-enforcement is engine-apparatus concern).
#   - Keep the critical-infrastructure block requiring multi-owner review.

